[
  "Levchin is cofounder and CEO of Affirm, a fintech lending company that helps people pay for items like cameras and dresses in installments.",
  "Before Affirm launched in 2014, Levchin cofounded PayPal, gaming company Slide and fertility-tracking app Glow.",
  "Levchin owns nearly 11% of Affirm. When it went public on January 13, 2021, the stock doubled, bringing its market value to $24 billion.",
  "In the quarter ending September 30, 2020, one-third of Affirm's revenue came from a single client: Peloton.",
  "In 1991, Levchin and his family emigrated from the Ukraine to Chicago as Jewish refugees; they arrived with just $700."
]